In it's current the DNC list allows political parties, pollsters, chatities and the like to still call you, the only ones being blocks are those trying to sell you something.  The argument is that in that form it essentially says that those still allowed to call have more of a right to say what they want than those not allowed to call.<br>
<br>
My solution to that would be that people signing up on the list designate who can and can't call.  Sure, it makes the list a bit more complex, but it lets telemarketers call those who don't mind them and keeps others from getting called by those that are currently exempt if they wish.  Nobody is made more &quot;right&quot; than the other as the choice is put in the hands of those with the phone. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138587" target="top">Hunter Denamian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
